85,"_updatedTicks":637458619213439653,"_scrollPosition":{"x":0.0,"y":0.0},"_boardWindow_SearchShow":true,"_taskWindow_ShowSubtask":true,"_treeWindow_SearchShow":true,"treeWindowShowSubtasksAnimation":{"m_Target":false,"speed":2.0,"m_Value":0.0},"_treeWindow_ShowSubtasks":false},{"_id":"4b93c3159eda4eccc6ad9d42965d66ae90e96f6a-47817c0b-a920-4751-ae3a-5dcf65cb41f9","_parentID":"4b93c3159eda4eccc6ad9d42965d66ae90e96f6a-a1e44b68-8a85-4adb-9281-788706c1276c","_lock":false,"_done":true,"_isParentSubtask":true,"_name":"Create a test script that will make the character sit","_description":"","_showSubtasks":true,"_tasksIds":[],"_hideCompletedChecklistItems":false,"_showTags":true,"_tagIds":[],"_showAssets":true,"_assets":[],"_showColors":false,"_colorIds":[],"_screenshot":[],"_showScreenshots":false,"_createdTicks":637458619264079997,"_updatedTicks":637458619598298055,"_scrollPosition":{"x":0.0,"y":0.0},"_boardWindow_SearchShow":true,"_taskWindow_ShowSubtask":true,"_treeWindow_SearchShow":true,"treeWindowShowSubtasksAnimation":{"m_Target":false,"speed":2.0,"m_Value":0.0},"_treeWindow_ShowSubtasks":false},{"_id":"4b93c3159eda4eccc6ad9d42965d66ae90e96f6a-c870f15c-5a27-4787-a417-20c12728f75e","_parentID":"4b93c3159eda4eccc6ad9d42965d66ae90e96f6a-a1e44b68-8a85-4adb-9281-788706c1276c","_lock":false,"_done":false,"_isParentSubtask":true,"_name":"Make the character move to the right position to sit","_description":"Goal is to have the character walk to the chair, turn around and sit.\n\n- Bake the Navmesh\n- Move NeoMan away from the chair\n- Add a NavMeshAgent to NeoMan\n- Add the NavMeshConnector to NeoMan\n- In the DevTest Script set the NavMeshAgent destination to the left foot position\n- Comment out the sitting code\n- Hit play\n- Character moves to sitting postiion\n\nWe now need to have the character turn around and then sit. But we don't want them to turn until they arrive at the right position.\n\nLet's start by having the character sit, we will worry about rotating correctly soon.\n\n- Create a state machine in the NavMeshConnector with Stationary, Moving , Arriving and Arrived states\n- In MoveTo enter the moving state\n- Create a Sit method into the HumanoidController\n- Change the Sitting Behaviour to call Sit and move the existing code into the new Sit method\n- Add arrivingDistance and Update method to connector that updates the states\n- Add an OnArriving callback parameter to the MoveTo method\n- Pass in the sit code when we arrive (via the callback)\n- Play\n\nThe character now moves to position but when they sit they are not sitting on the chair because the character does not rotate. Let's fix that now.\n\n- Add an OnArrived callback to the MoveTo\n- When calling MoveTo the current method should be used in OnArrived\n- The OnArriving should have the character rotate towards the direction of target position\n\nThis works reasonably well, but our character is sitting on the left front corner of the chair. To resolve this we need a different spot for the character to move to when sitting.\n\n- Add a new point for the character to move to that is beterrn the two feet postiions and a little nearer the chair\n- Ensure that the Z axis is pointing forwards from the chair\n- Make that the sit position in the SittingBehaviours script\n- Play\n\nWe are almost there now. The character sits in the center of the chair but they are on the edge of their seat. To resolve this we will add another callback, this time it will be called as soon as we enter the idlstationary state.\n\n- Add a callback to OnStationary when in the Stationary state\n- In the callback set a new destination with an offset in the Z axis\n\nSo nearly there. We should make it a little smoother.\n\n- move the sit animation to after the stationary callback code","_showSubtasks":true,"_tasksIds":[],"_hideCompletedChecklistItems":false,"_showTags":true,"_tagIds":[],"_showAssets":true,"_assets":[{"fileID":11500000,"guid":"84a5b9a99a7dae244a857775ff8603d5","type":3},{"fileI